{
  "text": "It is instructive to compare the solution presented above to the description of fundamental strings attached to a fivebrane as a Coulomb solution of the fivebrane BornInfeld theory [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In the latter case the parent brane is embedded in flat space and the worldvolume gauge field is simply that of a point charge. For n units of charge, the spike configuration that protrudes from the brane at the location of the charge is of the form",
  "correct_citation": {
